We’re excited to announce new predefined roles for [Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)](https://www.digitalocean.com/products/identity-access-management?utm_medium=email&utm_source=product&utm_campaign=rbac_announcement&utm_content=lead). With this feature release, customers will enjoy benefits including improved compliance, role adaptability, and cost savings. Starting today, in addition to the Owner, Member, and Biller roles, customers can now assign users the following roles:

- Modifier: Permits users to update but does not allow them to delete resources. This role is ideal for teams who wish to protect sensitive resources from deletion while still allowing members to manage them.
- Billing viewer: Permits read-only access to billing information only, giving users insight into billing details for cost analysis, transparency, and governance without exposing sensitive operational controls.
- Resource viewer: Permits read-only access to resources, ideal for audit or compliance purposes. Users with this role will not have permission to create, update, or delete resources.

[Explore New RBAC Roles](https://www.digitalocean.com/products/identity-access-management?utm_medium=email&utm_source=product&utm_campaign=rbac_announcement&utm_content=lead)
What Role-Based Access Control offers:

- Enhanced security: RBAC helps to protect against unauthorized access and potential security breaches by helping to ensure that only verified users can access sensitive resources, resulting in enhanced security.
- Operational efficiency: Leverage RBAC to streamline user provisioning and de-provisioning, reducing the manual workload for IT administrative staff and minimizing human errors.
- Cost savings: RBAC helps to lower administrative overhead by automating user management tasks and reducing the need for IT support.

In addition to predefined roles, we’re also working to deliver new RBAC features:

- Per-Bucket Spaces Access Keys - provides Spaces bucket access keys on a per-bucket basis.
- RBAC Custom Roles - allows customers to configure custom, persistent, reusable permission sets for their business needs which are not met by RBAC Standard Roles.

For now - if you want to learn more about predefined roles for RBAC, check out our comprehensive [product documentation.](https://docs.digitalocean.com/platform/teams/manage-membership/?utm_medium=email&utm_source=product&utm_campaign=rbac_announcement&utm_content=lead)

